id: pm-0zn9
title: "SDK deactivate test lifecycle: deactivateExtensionForTest + assertExtensionDeactivated helpers"
description: "Symmetric counterpart to activateExtensionForTest. The deactivate teardown lifecycle (pm-k1e4) and its per-hook timeout guard (pm-bujg) are first-class in core via deactivateExtensions, but package authors had no SDK helper to test their deactivate hook without importing private loader internals. Adds deactivateExtensionForTest (runs the real deactivateExtensions engine over one in-memory module) and assertExtensionDeactivated (assert clean teardown count), exports both from the public SDK testing surface, and extends the package-mode scaffold to demonstrate the full activate-then-deactivate lifecycle in the generated index.js + index.test.js. Completes the extension test-assertion surface alongside pm-6pmp and pm-4ltc."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:extensions","area:sdk",living-map,sdk-testing
