notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-21T12:30:24.618Z",claude-code-agent,"Implemented on branch feat/sdk-deactivate-test-lifecycle. Summary of changes:\n\n(1) src/sdk/testing.ts — added deactivateExtensionForTest(module, options) (teardown counterpart to activateExtensionForTest; runs the real deactivateExtensions engine over one in-memory load entry, returns ExtensionDeactivationResult) and assertExtensionDeactivated(result, expectation) (defaults assert one clean teardown / zero failures; accepts {deactivated, failed}). Extracted shared resolveTestExtensionName so both activate/deactivate helpers resolve the load-entry identity identically. New options: name, layer, activation (forwards a prior activation result so a failed-activation extension is skipped), deactivateTimeoutMs (forwarded as deactivate_timeout_ms).\n\n(2) src/sdk/index.ts — exported deactivateExtensionForTest, assertExtensionDeactivated, and types DeactivateExtensionForTestOptions, ExtensionDeactivationExpectation through the public SDK barrel (also reachable at @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk/testing).\n\n(3) src/cli/commands/extension/scaffold.ts — the starter index.js (both extension-only and package mode) now emits a documented deactivate teardown stub and wires it into the default export; the package-mode index.test.js gained a second test demonstrating deactivateExtensionForTest + assertExtensionDeactivated. READMEs updated for the lifecycle.\n\n(4) docs/SDK.md — documented both helpers in the testing-helper list + prose.\n\nTests: tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts (new helpers, all branches + barrel-equality) and tests/unit/extensions/extension-command.spec.ts (scaffold content assertions). Verified: 100% coverage (30431 stmts / 23754 branches / 5077 funcs / 29234 lines), 4808 tests green, typecheck + static + docs-skills gates green. Manual end-to-end: scaffolded a package in a temp dir, symlinked the repo as the peer SDK, ran node --test -> both activation and teardown tests pass; install + invoke + package doctor all green with zero unused capabilities."
close_reason: "Shipped deactivateExtensionForTest + assertExtensionDeactivated SDK testing helpers, exported them through the public SDK barrel, and extended the package scaffold to demonstrate the full activate/deactivate lifecycle. 100% coverage, all gates green, end-to-end verified in a temp package."
body: ""
